column4: Two children Grey and Parker. They all climb decently hard, 9’s and 10’s are on the table.
Traded me his Freino as a tip!
Spreading Bob’s ashes on the summit. Hawker
Super strong trans woman. Put her on more 10s if she comes back
Also super nice like her husband JC
German bikepacker in Rio. Bad language barrier; still learning multipitch and is very sketchy.
Climbed Everest and lots of other crazy things. Likes to climb best in Red Rocks. Not a tipper? Weird.
Climbed at Seneca starting 1999. Really nice guy and awesome to climb with.
Camp that summits Seneca once a year with SRMG
For folks I guided before I started this DB or folks I can’t remember anything about them
Really nice guy learning trad to become an independent leader and take nonprofit kids out climbing. Tall black guy who clearly used to lift
Great client, a little nervous on rappel but does great climbing
Son of Rob Lettan. Strong gym climber (16 y.o. in 2025)
Son of Gautam Iyer. Strong gym climber (16 y.o. in 2025)
Papa Reynolds. Commercial and Air Force pilot, super nice dude. Climbed with SRMG in 2019
Daughter of Justin Reynolds. Strong team kid, flashed Ye Gods on TR
Dating Olivia Stein. Really strong, V7 boulderer (not sure if that’s indoors or outdoors)
Climbed GSP about 15 years ago, wants to climb harder things!
Mid 50s, wants to get into more mountaineering type stuff. SRMG road trip Fall 2025
Nice woman in her mid 30s, used to climb super hard on sport. Wants to get into long sport stuff like at EPC
Gay dude in his early 30s, starting to get into outdoors climbing. Really fun to climb with, learns quick!
Married to Michelle Knight. Used to be big into alpine climbing, super technically capable but doesn’t climb very hard
Married to Matt Kearns, super nice folks!
From Northern California, been climbing over 10 years. Knows what he’s doing pretty well
